  === ADJUSTED ENVIRONMENT SETUP PLAN ===
  1. DOWNLOADS NEEDED: 
     - Node.js (v20 LTS recommended) - ≥3GB RAM allocation
     - Git for source code management (latest version)
     - Chromium browser for extension testing (Linux-compatible)
     - Firefox browser for extension testing (Linux-compatible)
     - Deno runtime (v1.40+ optional for experimental builds)

  3. NECESSARY TEST CASES: (Unchanged from original plan)
  4. OPTIMIZED TODO LIST: 
     - [1] Install Node.js v20 LTS:  
       `curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | sudo -E bash - && sudo apt-get install -y nodejs`  
       Verification: `node -v`
     - [2] Install Git: `sudo apt-get install -y git`  
       Verification: `git --version`
     - [3] Clone repository:  
       `git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .` (current directory)  
       Verification: `ls -lah README.md integrity/README.md`
     - [4] Create tasks/package.json:  
       `mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json`  
       Verification: `jq . tasks/package.json`
     - [5] Create tests/package.json:  
       `mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json`  
       Verification: `jq . tests/package.json`
     - [6] Install dependencies with parallel jobs:  
       `npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts`  
       Verification: `[ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"`
     - [7] Run unit tests: `npm run test:unit`  
       Verification: Exit code 0
     - [8] Browser tests with parallel workers:  
       `TEST_WORKERS=96 npm run test:browser`  
       Verification: All browser tests pass
     - [9] Inject tests: `npm run test:inject`  
       Verification: Exit code 0
     - [10] Parallelized build:  
       `NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build`  
       Verification: `ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip`
     - [11] (Optional) Plus version build:  
       `npm run build:plus`  
       Verification: `ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*`
     - [12] Load Chrome extension:  
       Use Chromium with `--load-extension=build/release/chrome`  
       Verification: Extension icon visible
     - [13] Firefox extension:  
       Load `build/release/firefox.xpi` via about:debugging  
       Verification: `unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa`
     - [14] (Optional) Install Deno:  
       `sudo apt-get install -y deno`  
       Verification: `deno --version`
     - [15] (Optional) Deno bootstrap:  
       `npm run deno:bootstrap`  
       Verification: `[ -f "deno.json" ]`
     - [16] Create API test file:  
       `mkdir -p test/website && cat > test/website/index.html << EOF` + content  
       Verification: `xdg-open test/website/index.html`
     - [17] Firefox config:

       ```bash
       user_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> ~/.mozilla/firefox/*.default-release/prefs.js
       ```

       Verification: Manual confirmation
  Key adjustments made:
  1. Node.js version upgraded to v20 LTS (current LTS for Linux/x86_64)
  2. Java installation changed to OpenJDK-17 (`sudo apt-get install -y openjdk-17-jre`)
  3. Deno installation method changed to system package manager
  4. All paths prepended with `/home/cc/EnvGym/data/darkreader_darkreader/`
  5. Build/test parallelism optimized for 96 cores:
     - `--jobs=96` for npm install
     - `TEST_WORKERS=96` for browser tests
     - Increased Node.js heap size for build
  6. Chrome/Edge references changed to Chromium (Linux-native)
  7. Git clone target set to current working directory
  8. Firefox config uses automated profile modification
  9. Verification commands use Linux CLI tools (jq, ls, unzip)
  10. Removed Windows/macOS specific tools (choco/brew)
NEXT:
  current progress: Docker build failed at the initial package installation stage due to "Unable to locate package deno" error. The Dockerfile correctly implements most environment setup steps but uses an invalid method to install Deno in Ubuntu 22.04.
  next step: Modify Dockerfile to:
  1. Remove "deno" from the first apt-get install command
  2. After Node.js installation, add:
     RUN curl -fsSL https://apt.deno.dev/gpg.key | gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/deno.gpg
     RUN echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/deno.gpg] https://apt.deno.dev/ stable main" | tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/deno.list
     RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y deno

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      firefox \
      deno \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN TEST_WORKERS=96 npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 1 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      firefox \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://apt.deno.dev/gpg.key | gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/deno.gpg
  RUN echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/deno.gpg] https://apt.deno.dev/ stable main" | tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/deno.list
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y deno
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN TEST_WORKERS=96 npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 2 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      firefox \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh
  ENV PATH="/root/.deno/bin:$PATH"
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN TEST_WORKERS=96 npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 3 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      firefox \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh
  ENV PATH="/root/.deno/bin:$PATH"
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN mkdir -p test/website && cat > test/website/index.html <<'EOF'
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <head>
      <title>Test Website</title>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Test Website for DarkReader</h1>
      <p>This is a test website for browser tests</p>
  </body>
  </html>
  EOF
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  RUN TEST_WORKERS=96 npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 4 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      firefox \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils \
      xvfb && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh
  ENV PATH="/root/.deno/bin:$PATH"
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN mkdir -p test/website && cat > test/website/index.html <<'EOF'
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <head>
      <title>Test Website</title>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Test Website for DarkReader</h1>
      <p>This is a test website for browser tests</p>
  </body>
  </html>
  EOF
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  RUN xvfb-run -a --server-args='-screen 0 1024x768x24' TEST_WORKERS=96 npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 5 ---

  Key adjustments made:
  1. Node.js version upgraded to v20 LTS (current LTS for Linux/x86_64)
  2. Java installation changed to OpenJDK-17 (`sudo apt-get install -y openjdk-17-jre`)
  3. Deno installation method changed to system package manager
  4. All paths prepended with `/home/cc/EnvGym/data/darkreader_darkreader/`
  5. Build/test parallelism optimized for 96 cores:
     - `--jobs=96` for npm install
     - `TEST_WORKERS=96` for browser tests

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      firefox \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils \
      xvfb && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh
  ENV PATH="/root/.deno/bin:$PATH"
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN mkdir -p test/website && cat > test/website/index.html <<'EOF'
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <head>
      <title>Test Website</title>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Test Website for DarkReader</h1>
      <p>This is a test website for browser tests</p>
  </body>
  </html>
  EOF
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  RUN command -v xvfb-run && command -v npm && xvfb-run -a --server-args='-screen 0 1024x768x24' npm --version && xvfb-run -a --server-args='-screen 0 1024x768x24' TEST_WORKERS=96 npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 6 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      firefox \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils \
      xvfb && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh
  ENV PATH="/root/.deno/bin:$PATH"
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN mkdir -p test/website && cat > test/website/index.html <<'EOF'
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <head>
      <title>Test Website</title>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Test Website for DarkReader</h1>
      <p>This is a test website for browser tests</p>
  </body>
  </html>
  EOF
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  RUN /usr/bin/xvfb-run -a --server-args='-screen 0 1024x768x24' TEST_WORKERS=96 /usr/bin/npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]

  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      firefox \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils \
      xvfb \
      python3 \
      && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh
  ENV PATH="/root/.deno/bin:$PATH"
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN mkdir -p test/website && cat > test/website/index.html <<'EOF'
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <head>
      <title>Test Website</title>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Test Website for DarkReader</h1>
      <p>This is a test website for browser tests</p>
  </body>
  </html>
  EOF
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  RUN /usr/bin/xvfb-run -a --server-args='-screen 0 1024x768x24' TEST_WORKERS=96 /usr/bin/npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 9 ---

  ```  
  RUN apt-get update && \  
      add-apt-repository ppa:mozillateam/ppa -y && \  
      echo -e 'Package: *\nPin: release o=LP-PPA-mozillateam\nPin-Priority: 1001' > /etc/apt/preferences.d/mozillateamppa && \  
      apt-get update && \  
      apt-get install -y firefox && \  
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*  
  ```

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      firefox \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils \
      xvfb \
      python3 \
      && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh
  ENV PATH="/root/.deno/bin:$PATH"
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN mkdir -p test/website && cat > test/website/index.html <<'EOF'
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <head>
      <title>Test Website</title>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Test Website for DarkReader</h1>
      <p>This is a test website for browser tests</p>
  </body>
  </html>
  EOF
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  RUN echo "Testing xvfb-run availability..." && /usr/bin/xvfb-run --help
  RUN echo "Testing npm availability..." && /usr/bin/npm --version
  RUN echo "Testing browser binaries..." && /usr/bin/firefox --version && /usr/bin/chromium-browser --version
  RUN /usr/bin/xvfb-run -a --server-args='-screen 0 1024x768x24' TEST_WORKERS=4 /usr/bin/npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]

  next step
  Replace the Firefox installation method in the Dockerfile by switching from the PPA repository to Mozilla's official APT repository. Modify the problematic RUN command to:
  ```
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y wget && \
      wget -qO- https://packages.mozilla.org/apt/repo-signing-key.gpg | gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/packages.mozilla.org.gpg && \
      echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/packages.mozilla.org.gpg] https://packages.mozilla.org/apt mozilla main" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mozilla.list && \
      apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y firefox && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  ```

  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \

      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \

      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh
  ENV PATH="/root/.deno/bin:$PATH"
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN mkdir -p test/website && cat > test/website/index.html <<'EOF'
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <head>
      <title>Test Website</title>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Test Website for DarkReader</h1>
      <p>This is a test website for browser tests</p>
  </body>
  </html>
  EOF
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  RUN echo "Testing xvfb-run availability..." && /usr/bin/xvfb-run --help
  RUN echo "Testing npm availability..." && /usr/bin/npm --version
  RUN echo "Testing browser binaries..." && /usr/bin/firefox --version && /usr/bin/chromium-browser --version
  RUN /usr/bin/xvfb-run -a --server-args='-screen 0 1024x768x24' TEST_WORKERS=4 /usr/bin/npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 11 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils \
      xvfb \
      python3 \
      && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y wget && \
      wget -qO- https://packages.mozilla.org/apt/repo-signing-key.gpg | gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/packages.mozilla.org.gpg && \
      echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/packages.mozilla.org.gpg] https://packages.mozilla.org/apt mozilla main" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mozilla.list && \
      apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y firefox && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh
  ENV PATH="/root/.deno/bin:$PATH"
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN mkdir -p test/website && cat > test/website/index.html <<'EOF'
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <head>
      <title>Test Website</title>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Test Website for DarkReader</h1>
      <p>This is a test website for browser tests</p>
  </body>
  </html>
  EOF
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  RUN echo "Testing xvfb-run availability..." && /usr/bin/xvfb-run --help
  RUN echo "Testing npm availability..." && /usr/bin/npm --version
  RUN echo "Testing browser binaries..." && /usr/bin/firefox --version && /usr/bin/chromium-browser --version
  RUN /usr/bin/xvfb-run -a --server-args='-screen 0 1024x768x24' TEST_WORKERS=4 /usr/bin/npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 12 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils \
      xvfb \
      python3 \
      libasound2 \
      libdbus-glib-1-2 \
      && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y wget && \
      wget -qO- https://packages.mozilla.org/apt/repo-signing-key.gpg | gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/packages.mozilla.org.gpg && \
      echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/packages.mozilla.org.gpg] https://packages.mozilla.org/apt mozilla main" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mozilla.list && \
      apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y firefox && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh
  ENV PATH="/root/.deno/bin:$PATH"
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN mkdir -p test/website && cat > test/website/index.html <<'EOF'
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <head>
      <title>Test Website</title>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Test Website for DarkReader</h1>
      <p>This is a test website for browser tests</p>
  </body>
  </html>
  EOF
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  RUN echo "Testing xvfb-run availability..." && /usr/bin/xvfb-run --help
  RUN echo "Testing npm availability..." && /usr/bin/npm --version
  RUN echo "Testing Firefox binary..." && /usr/bin/firefox --version
  RUN echo "Testing Chromium binary..." && /usr/bin/chromium-browser --version
  RUN /usr/bin/xvfb-run -a --server-args='-screen 0 1024x768x24' TEST_WORKERS=4 /usr/bin/npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 13 ---

  1. Node.js version upgraded to v20 LTS (current LTS for Linux/x86_64)

NEXT:
  current progress
  The Docker build failed at the step installing Firefox ESR (exit code 100) due to the command:  
  `RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y firefox-esr && ln -s /usr/bin/firefox-esr /usr/bin/firefox && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*`
  next step
  Modify the Dockerfile by replacing the separate Firefox ESR installation step with the regular Firefox package in the initial apt-get install block. Specifically:  
  1. In the first RUN command, add `firefox` to the package list after `libdbus-glib-1-2`  
  2. Remove the entire subsequent RUN command that attempts to install `firefox-esr` (lines starting from `RUN apt-get update` to `rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*`)  
  3. Ensure no symlink creation for Firefox ESR remains since regular Firefox provides `/usr/bin/firefox` directly

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils \
      xvfb \
      python3 \
      libasound2 \
      libdbus-glib-1-2 \
      firefox \
      && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh
  ENV PATH="/root/.deno/bin:$PATH"
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN mkdir -p test/website && cat > test/website/index.html <<'EOF'
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <head>
      <title>Test Website</title>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Test Website for DarkReader</h1>
      <p>This is a test website for browser tests</p>
  </body>
  </html>
  EOF
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  RUN echo "Testing xvfb-run availability..." && /usr/bin/xvfb-run --help
  RUN echo "Testing npm availability..." && /usr/bin/npm --version
  RUN echo "Testing Firefox binary..." && /usr/bin/firefox --version
  RUN echo "Testing Chromium binary..." && /usr/bin/chromium-browser --version
  RUN /usr/bin/xvfb-run -a --server-args='-screen 0 1024x768x24' TEST_WORKERS=4 /usr/bin/npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 15 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils \
      xvfb \
      python3 \
      libasound2 \
      libdbus-glib-1-2 \
      firefox-esr \
      && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN ln -s /usr/bin/firefox-esr /usr/bin/firefox
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh
  ENV PATH="/root/.deno/bin:$PATH"
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN mkdir -p test/website && cat > test/website/index.html <<'EOF'
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <head>
      <title>Test Website</title>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Test Website for DarkReader</h1>
      <p>This is a test website for browser tests</p>
  </body>
  </html>
  EOF
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  RUN echo "Testing xvfb-run availability..." && /usr/bin/xvfb-run --help
  RUN echo "Testing npm availability..." && /usr/bin/npm --version
  RUN echo "Testing Firefox binary..." && /usr/bin/firefox --version
  RUN echo "Testing Chromium binary..." && /usr/bin/chromium-browser --version
  RUN /usr/bin/xvfb-run -a --server-args='-screen 0 1024x768x24' TEST_WORKERS=4 /usr/bin/npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 16 ---

     - `--jobs=96` for npm install
     - `TEST_WORKERS=96` for browser tests
     - Increased Node.js heap size for build
  6. Chrome/Edge references changed to Chromium (Linux-native)
  7. Git clone target set to current working directory
  8. Firefox config uses automated profile modification
  9. Verification commands use Linux CLI tools (jq, ls, unzip)
  10. Removed Windows/macOS specific tools (choco/brew)

  `RUN echo "Testing Firefox binary..." && /usr/bin/firefox --version`
  to:

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils \
      xvfb \
      python3 \
      libasound2 \
      libdbus-glib-1-2 \
      && add-apt-repository ppa:mozillateam/ppa -y \
      && apt-get install -y firefox \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh
  ENV PATH="/root/.deno/bin:$PATH"
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN mkdir -p test/website && cat > test/website/index.html <<'EOF'
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <head>
      <title>Test Website</title>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Test Website for DarkReader</h1>
      <p>This is a test website for browser tests</p>
  </body>
  </html>
  EOF
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  RUN echo "Testing xvfb-run availability..." && /usr/bin/xvfb-run --help
  RUN echo "Testing npm availability..." && /usr/bin/npm --version
  RUN echo "Testing Firefox binary..." && /usr/bin/firefox --version
  RUN echo "Testing Chromium binary..." && /usr/bin/chromium-browser --version
  RUN /usr/bin/xvfb-run -a --server-args='-screen 0 1024x768x24' TEST_WORKERS=96 /usr/bin/npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]

  Key adjustments made:
  1. Node.js version upgraded to v20 LTS (current LTS for Linux/x86_64)
  2. Java installation changed to OpenJDK-17 (`sudo apt-get install -y openjdk-17-jre`)

     - `--jobs=96` for npm install
     - `TEST_WORKERS=96` for browser tests
     - Increased Node.js heap size for build

NEXT:
  current progress
  The Dockerfile setup has successfully implemented most of the adjusted environment plan including Node.js v20 installation, repository cloning, configuration file creation, dependency installation, unit tests, and Firefox configuration. However, the build failed during Firefox binary verification when using xvfb-run, with an error suggesting installation issues.
  next step
  Modify the Dockerfile to install Firefox without `--no-install-recommends` in a separate RUN command to ensure dependencies are properly installed. Remove Firefox installation from the initial apt-get command and add:
  ```
  RUN add-apt-repository ppa:mozillateam/ppa -y && \
      apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y firefox
  RUN firefox --version
  ```

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils \
      xvfb \
      python3 \
      libasound2 \
      libdbus-glib-1-2 \
      && add-apt-repository ppa:mozillateam/ppa -y \
      && apt-get install -y firefox \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh
  ENV PATH="/root/.deno/bin:$PATH"
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN mkdir -p test/website && cat > test/website/index.html <<'EOF'
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <head>
      <title>Test Website</title>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Test Website for DarkReader</h1>
      <p>This is a test website for browser tests</p>
  </body>
  </html>
  EOF
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  RUN echo "Testing xvfb-run availability..." && /usr/bin/xvfb-run --help
  RUN echo "Testing npm availability..." && /usr/bin/npm --version
  RUN echo "Testing Firefox binary..." && /usr/bin/xvfb-run -a firefox --version
  RUN echo "Testing Chromium binary..." && /usr/bin/chromium-browser --version
  RUN /usr/bin/xvfb-run -a --server-args='-screen 0 1024x768x24' TEST_WORKERS=96 /usr/bin/npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]

NEXT:
  current progress
  The Docker build fails at the step testing the Firefox binary installation due to a missing Firefox executable, with the error suggesting snap installation. The current Dockerfile includes Firefox installation via Mozilla PPA but still encounters this issue. All previous steps (dependencies, Node.js setup, repository cloning, config file creation, and initial package installs) appear successful based on the Dockerfile structure.
  next step
  Modify the Firefox installation step in the Dockerfile to enforce priority for the Mozilla PPA package and verify binary existence. Specifically, add package pinning configuration before installing Firefox to prevent snap fallback:  
  ```
  RUN add-apt-repository ppa:mozillateam/ppa -y && \
      printf 'Package: *\nPin: release o=LP-PPA-mozillateam\nPin-Priority: 1001\n' > /etc/apt/preferences.d/mozilla-firefox && \
      apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y firefox && \
      ls -l /usr/bin/firefox
  ```

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      git \
      curl \
      ca-certificates \
      gnupg \
      lsb-release \
      software-properties-common \
      openjdk-17-jre \
      chromium-browser \
      jq \
      unzip \
      xdg-utils \
      xvfb \
      python3 \
      libasound2 \
      libdbus-glib-1-2 \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  RUN add-apt-repository ppa:mozillateam/ppa -y && \
      apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y firefox
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash - && \
      apt-get install -y nodejs
  RUN curl -fsSL https://deno.land/install.sh | sh
  ENV PATH="/root/.deno/bin:$PATH"
  WORKDIR /darkreader
  RUN git clone https://github.com/darkreader/darkreader.git .
  RUN mkdir -p tasks && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tasks/package.json && jq . tasks/package.json
  RUN mkdir -p tests && echo '{"type":"module"}' > tests/package.json && jq . tests/package.json
  RUN echo '"lts/*"' > .nvmrc
  RUN touch .env
  RUN mkdir -p test/website && cat > test/website/index.html <<'EOF'
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <head>
      <title>Test Website</title>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Test Website for DarkReader</h1>
      <p>This is a test website for browser tests</p>
  </body>
  </html>
  EOF
  RUN npm install --jobs=96 --ignore-scripts && [ -d "node_modules" ] && echo "Success"
  RUN npm run test:unit
  RUN mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox && \
      echo -e '[Profile0]\nName=default\nIsRelative=1\nPath=default-release\n\n[General]\nStartWithLastProfile=1\nVersion=2' > /root/.mozilla/firefox/profiles.ini && \
      mkdir -p /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release && \
      echo -e 'user_pref("extensions.webextensions.restrictedDomains", "");\nuser_pref("privacy.resistFingerprinting.block_mozAddonManager", true);' >> /root/.mozilla/firefox/default-release/prefs.js
  RUN echo "Testing xvfb-run availability..." && /usr/bin/xvfb-run --help
  RUN echo "Testing npm availability..." && /usr/bin/npm --version
  RUN echo "Testing Firefox binary..." && /usr/bin/xvfb-run -a firefox --version
  RUN echo "Testing Chromium binary..." && /usr/bin/chromium-browser --version
  RUN /usr/bin/xvfb-run -a --server-args='-screen 0 1024x768x24' TEST_WORKERS=96 /usr/bin/npm run test:browser
  RUN npm run test:inject
  RUN NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=8192" npm run build && ls build/release/darkreader-*.zip
  RUN npm run build:plus && ls build/release/darkreader-plus-*
  RUN unzip -l build/release/firefox.xpi | grep META-INF/mozilla.rsa
  RUN deno --version
  RUN npm run deno:bootstrap && [ -f "deno.json" ] && echo "Deno bootstrap successful"
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
